"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7422903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7422903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104plb1718886888754.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/plb1718886888754.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/plb1718886888754.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"flj1665703009239\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $prompt\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"flj1665703009239___prompt_284561\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return or set the position for the cursor in the Form when the current ProcScript module ends.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"flj1665703009239__topic_d88163e1_d88164e1_d88165e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"flj1665703009239__p_d88166e1_d88167e1_d88168e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"flj1665703009239__p_d88169e1_d88170e1_d88171e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Field</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"flj1665703009239__topic_d58722e1_d58723e1_d58724e1_d58725e1_d58726e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d882135e78\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"flj1665703009239__li_d35345e1_d35346e1_d35347e1\">String that contains the name of the field where the cursor will be positioned when control returns to the structure editor. The returned value is in the format <code class=\"ph codeph\">FIELD.ENTITY.MODEL</code>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"flj1665703009239__li_d35348e1_d35349e1_d35350e1\">Empty string (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code>) if the default prompting sequence is in effect.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"flj1665703009239__topic_d58727e1_d58728e1_d58729e1_d58730e1_d58731e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d882135e99\">\n                       \n Use\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"flj1665703009239__p_d88178e1_d88179e1_d88180e1\">Use in Form components. If used in other components, it is ignored.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"flj1665703009239__note_w2569ab1b7b7b5_w2570ab1b7b7_w2571ab1b7_w2572ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span> should not be used in I/O-related triggers that set the\n            active path, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Retrieve</span>, because <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span> can\n            change the active path. As a result, the sequence of fired triggers will be different\n            from the expected sequence, and some triggers will not fire at all, for example\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">loseFocus</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">getFocus</span>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"flj1665703009239__topic_d58732e1_d58733e1_d58734e1_d58735e1_d58736e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d882135e125\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"flj1665703009239__p_d88184e1_d88185e1_d88186e1\">The function <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span> can be used to define the field where the cursor should be positioned when the current ProcScript module ends. When the name of a field is assigned to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$prompt</span>, the cursor is positioned at that field when control returns to the structure editor.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"flj1665703009239__p_d88187e1_d88188e1_d88189e1\">When executed, Uniface automatically scrolls to the field where the cursor is positioned. If the field has an associated label, Uniface scrolls to show the entire field including the associated label. This is especially useful in mobile applications in which some fields may not be immediately visible. You can disable this automatic scrolling using the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PROMPT_SCROLL</span> assignment setting.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"flj1665703009239__section_n4q_ndl_5bc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d882135e147\">Example: Using $prompt </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The next trigger ProcScript below defines conditional field prompting. If\n            the invoice date is greater than the system date, the cursor goes automatically to the\n            CORRESP entity. Otherwise, the cursor goes to the next field in the default prompting\n            sequence.</p>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"flj1665703009239__pre_dnf_pdl_5bc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger next\nif (INVDATE &gt; $date)\n $prompt = TEXT.CORRESP\n message \"Invoice is overdue. Write a reminder letter.\"\nendif\nend; next</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cib1665702561871.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Active Path for Runtime Processing</a><p>The active path determines where processing is applied in a runtime component, and the order in which it occurs. It leads from the current occurrence of the outermost entity down to the current occurrence of the innermost entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wwd1665702723271.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$PROMPT_SCROLL</a><p>Enable or disable automatic scrolling for the $prompt ProcScript function.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7422903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$prompt Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $prompt Return or set the position for the cursor in the Form when the current ProcScript module ends. $prompt $prompt = Field Return Values String that contains the name of the field where the cursor will be positioned when control returns to the structure editor. The returned value is in the format FIELD.ENTITY.MODEL . Empty string ( \"\" ) if the default prompting sequence is in effect. Use Use in Form components. If used in other components, it is ignored. Note: $prompt should not be used in I/O-related triggers that set the active path, such as Retrieve , because $prompt can change the active path. As a result, the sequence of fired triggers will be different from the expected sequence, and some triggers will not fire at all, for example loseFocus and getFocus . Description The function $prompt can be used to define the field where the cursor should be positioned when the current ProcScript module ends. When the name of a field is assigned to $prompt , the cursor is positioned at that field when control returns to the structure editor. When executed, Uniface automatically scrolls to the field where the cursor is positioned. If the field has an associated label, Uniface scrolls to show the entire field including the associated label. This is especially useful in mobile applications in which some fields may not be immediately visible. You can disable this automatic scrolling using the $PROMPT_SCROLL assignment setting. Example: Using $prompt The next trigger ProcScript below defines conditional field prompting. If the invoice date is greater than the system date, the cursor goes automatically to the CORRESP entity. Otherwise, the cursor goes to the next field in the default prompting sequence. trigger next if (INVDATE > $date) $prompt = TEXT.CORRESP message \"Invoice is overdue. Write a reminder letter.\" endif end; next Copy Related Links Active Path for Runtime Processing The active path determines where processing is applied in a runtime component, and the order in which it occurs. It leads from the current occurrence of the outermost entity down to the current occurrence of the innermost entity. $PROMPT_SCROLL Enable or disable automatic scrolling for the $prompt ProcScript function. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}